== Reception ==
[[File:Silver and Midnight Silver Tesla Model 3s.jpg|thumb|Tesla Model 3s in colors Silver Metallic (left) and Midnight Silver (right)]]
Car-design columnist and former car designer for [[General Motors|GM]] [[Robert Cumberford]] said the Model 3 "is an excellent design" and praised the front fascia skin that he thinks is superior to the black plastic simulated grille of the pre-refresh Model S.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.automobilemag.com/news/tesla-model-3-design/ |title=By Design: Tesla Model 3 |author-link=Robert Cumberford |first=Robert |last=Cumberford |date=September 5, 2016 |access-date=October 7, 2016 |magazine=[[Automobile (magazine)|Automobile]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009145839/http://www.automobilemag.com/news/tesla-model-3-design/ |archive-date=October 9, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Excellent">{{cite news |title = Tesla Model 3's design praised by famed car design critic Robert Cumberford |work = Electrek |url = https://electrek.co/2016/09/05/tesla-model-3-design-praised-robert-cumberford/ |first = Fred |last = Lambert |date = September 5, 2016 |access-date = September 15, 2016 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160910050347/https://electrek.co/2016/09/05/tesla-model-3-design-praised-robert-cumberford/ |archive-date = September 10, 2016 |url-status = live }}</ref> Cumberford praised the Model 3's minimalist design, and "elegant simplicity" akin to [[Apple, Inc.|Apple]] products.<ref name=Cumberford2018b/> Although he criticized the car's spoiler, he said the Model 3 has a design that would age well, and "in 10 years it will still look contemporary and beautifully understated, not old and irrelevant."<ref name=Cumberford2018b/>

''[[Motor Trend]]'' said the nose was controversial and polarizing, but probably intentionally so.<ref name=MTT20160510>{{cite news |url=http://www.motortrend.com/news/tesla-model-3-photos-analysis/ |title=Exclusive Tesla Photos and Expert Analysis on Model 3 Design and Tech |first=Brian |last=Vance |magazine=[[Motor Trend]] |location=US |date=May 10, 2016 |accessdate=May 15, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516165403/http://www.motortrend.com/news/tesla-model-3-photos-analysis/ |archive-date=May 16, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' and others compared the Model 3 to the [[Ford Model T]] for its intended affordability as a volume-produced electric vehicle<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2016/04/tesla-model-3-electric-car |title=The Tesla Model 3 Wants to be the Millennial Model T |first=Brett |last=Berk |magazine=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |location=US |date=April 1, 2016 |access-date=June 5, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170613180858/http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2016/04/tesla-model-3-electric-car |archive-date=June 13, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.instrument.com/articles/tesla-and-the-model-t|title=Tesla and the Model T – Learning from the Past to Invent the Future|author=Carson Smith|publisher=Instrument|access-date=June 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170627171407/http://www.instrument.com/articles/tesla-and-the-model-t|archive-date=June 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://electrek.co/2017/05/24/tesla-vs-fords-model-t-revolution/|title=Tesla's deliveries are still tracking close to Ford's Model T revolution|author=Fred Lambert|date=May 24, 2017|publisher=Electrek|access-date=June 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801034048/https://electrek.co/2017/05/24/tesla-vs-fords-model-t-revolution/|archive-date=August 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="roy-20171107"/> and for its limited set of options, namely range, wheels and exterior color of which all but black costs extra.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/cars/tesla-model-3-will-debut-with-only-two-options-color-and-wheels/2017/06/07/174f9672-4bd9-11e7-987c-42ab5745db2e_story.html |website= Washington Post |first= Richard |last= Read |title= Tesla Model 3 will debut with only two options: color and wheels |date= June 7, 2017 |accessdate= August 1, 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170801054507/http://www.washingtonpost.com/cars/tesla-model-3-will-debut-with-only-two-options-color-and-wheels/2017/06/07/174f9672-4bd9-11e7-987c-42ab5745db2e_story.html |archive-date= August 1, 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= https://electrek.co/2017/07/29/tesla-model-3-production-colors/ |website= electrek.co |first= Fred |last= Lambert |title= A look at all Tesla Model 3 production colors |date= July 29, 2017 |accessdate= August 1, 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170801013727/https://electrek.co/2017/07/29/tesla-model-3-production-colors/ |archive-date= August 1, 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref> Automotive journalist [[Doug DeMuro]] said the Model 3 was better, though $2,000 more expensive, than the [[BMW 3 Series (F30)#Petrol engines|BMW 340i]] and that it was the "coolest car of the year," later clarifying that this was based on the "long waiting lists, obsessive interest and news stories."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.autotrader.com/car-video/heres-why-the-tesla-model-3-is-the-coolest-car-of-2017-270672 |website=AutoTrader.com |first=Doug |last=DeMuro |title=Here's Why the Tesla Model 3 Is the Coolest Car of 2017 |date=November 6, 2017 |accessdate=November 7, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107121625/https://www.autotrader.com/car-video/heres-why-the-tesla-model-3-is-the-coolest-car-of-2017-270672 |archive-date=November 7, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Alex Roy]] said that DeMuro's review had concentrated on hardware details and missed out on the bigger picture.<ref name="roy-20171107">{{cite web|url=http://www.thedrive.com/opinion/15838/the-truth-behind-doug-demuros-tesla-model-3-review|title=The Truth Behind Doug DeMuro's Tesla Model 3 Review|website=[[/Drive]]|first=Alex|last=Roy|authorlink=Alex Roy|date=November 7, 2017|accessdate=November 10, 2017|quote=DeMuro blew his Model 3 review by ignoring Tesla's biggest secret. … If you want to understand the Model 3, read retired auto exec … [[Bob Lutz (businessman)|Bob Lutz]]'s screed on the future of the auto sector. … The Model 3, both in design and marketing, is beyond genius.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171109191829/http://www.thedrive.com/opinion/15838/the-truth-behind-doug-demuros-tesla-model-3-review|archive-date=November 9, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

Automotive-industry analyst Toni Sacconaghi of [[AllianceBernstein]] said after driving one of the early Tesla vehicles in November 2017 that "Overall, we found the Model 3 to be a compelling offering, and believe it is likely to further galvanize the overall Electric Vehicle category." He was less impressed with build quality of the test samples. "Fit and finish on the two demo cars we saw—perhaps not surprisingly—was relatively poor." He said that there were quality issues at first with the Model X which led to some concern. "This is going to be a much, much higher-volume car, and if there are any quality issues, that could overwhelm the service centers and undermine the Tesla brand." Nonetheless, Sacconaghi was impressed with the ride quality, performance and interior space, and concluded that the 3 "risks cannibalizing the [much more expensive] Model S going forward."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/business/hiltzik/la-fi-hiltzik-tesla-quality-20171114-story.html|title=Tesla's new Model 3 sedan has test drivers swooning – but quality issues lurk on the horizon|first=Michael|last=Hiltzik|date=November 14, 2017|access-date=January 5, 2018|via=LA Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105035824/http://www.latimes.com/business/hiltzik/la-fi-hiltzik-tesla-quality-20171114-story.html|archive-date=January 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

''[[Road & Track]]''{{'}}s Bob Sorokanich said the "Model 3 proves that Tesla is thinking far beyond the edges of the Model S and X. Stepping out of the 3, you realize that, as far as the S and X pushed the envelope, they were always meant as intermediaries, stepping stones designed to draw people away from comfortable convention and into the future of the automobile. ... The Model 3 is Tesla at its most unabashed. It's an automaker finally willing to abandon the [[skeuomorph]]ism of a false radiator grille, the tradition of a driver-oriented gauge panel."<ref name="r&t20180112">{{cite news |url=http://www.roadandtrack.com/new-cars/first-drives/a15070866/tesla-model-3-test-drive-review/ |title=Tesla Model 3: The Road & Track Review : Can Tesla's most affordable model kick-start the electric car revolution? |author=Bob Sorokanich |work=[[Road & Track]] |date=January 12, 2018 |accessdate=January 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112234745/http://www.roadandtrack.com/new-cars/first-drives/a15070866/tesla-model-3-test-drive-review/ |archive-date=January 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In early 2019, [[Kelley Blue Book]] announced that the Tesla Model 3 was the winner of the "Best Resale Value Award" for all automobiles in the US market "with a projected 69.3% resale value after 36 months and 48.7% after 60 months."<ref name=trati20190124>{{cite web|url=https://www.teslarati.com/used-tesla-model-3-model-x-resale-value-kelley-blue-book-kbb/|title=Tesla Model 3, Model X take top spots for EV with highest resale value by KBB|first=Dacia J.|last=Ferris|date=January 25, 2019|publisher=|access-date=January 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190126000712/https://www.teslarati.com/used-tesla-model-3-model-x-resale-value-kelley-blue-book-kbb/|archive-date=January 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> <!--market for used cars https://cleantechnica.com/2019/01/06/tesla-model-3-used-car-stats-as-depressing-for-bmw-audi-as-new-car-sales/ -->

=== Awards ===
''[[Popular Mechanics]]'' named the Tesla Model 3 as the magazine's 2018 Car of the Year.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.popularmechanics.com/cars/gmp19605464/best-cars-2018/ |title=The 2018 Automotive Excellence Awards |first=Ezra |last=Dyer |magazine=Popular Mechanics |location=US |date=March 28, 2018 |access-date=April 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180411105701/https://www.popularmechanics.com/cars/gmp19605464/best-cars-2018/ |archive-date=April 11, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Model 3 was given the 2018 Design of the Year award by ''[[Automobile (magazine)|Automobile]]'' magazine.<ref name="Cumberford2018b">{{cite news |url=http://www.automobilemag.com/news/2018-design-of-the-year-tesla-model-3/ |title=2018 Design of the Year: Tesla Model 3 |first=Robert |last=Cumberford |publisher=Automobile |location=US |date=January 17, 2018 |access-date=April 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412003051/http://www.automobilemag.com/news/2018-design-of-the-year-tesla-model-3/ |archive-date=April 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In the United Kingdom, the Model 3 was named 2019 Car of the Year by ''[[Auto Express]]'' magazine,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.autoexpress.co.uk/tesla/model-3/107363/car-of-the-year-2019-tesla-model-3|title=Car of the Year 2019: Tesla Model 3|publisher=Dennis Publishing|location=UK|date=July 10, 2019|access-date=July 14, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714004442/https://www.autoexpress.co.uk/tesla/model-3/107363/car-of-the-year-2019-tesla-model-3|archive-date=July 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and 2020 Car of the Year by ''Parkers'' magazine, where it was also named "Best Electric Car" and "Best Company Car", and won the "Best Safety" award for any vehicle on the market.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parkers.co.uk/car-awards/|title=Parkers New Car Awards 2020|last=|first=|date=October 2019|website=Parkers|publisher=Bauer Media|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022063211/https://www.parkers.co.uk/car-awards/|archive-date=October 22, 2019|access-date=October 22, 2019}}</ref>

The Model 3 won best mid-size car in the 2019 [[Das Goldene Lenkrad]] Golden Steering Wheel awards.<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.axelspringer.com/en/press-releases/mobility-requires-freedom-the-golden-steering-wheel-2019-bild-am-sonntag-and-auto-bild-award-the-best-cars |title=“Mobility requires freedom”: THE GOLDEN STEERING WHEEL 2019: BILD am SONNTAG and AUTO-BILD award the best cars |work=Axel Springer |location=Germany |date=November 13, 2019 |access-date=November 13, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113074602/https://www.axelspringer.com/en/press-releases/mobility-requires-freedom-the-golden-steering-wheel-2019-bild-am-sonntag-and-auto-bild-award-the-best-cars |archive-date=November 13, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>

The Model 3 was named the top rated electric car of 2019 by [[Edmunds (company)|Edmunds]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://insideevs.com/news/387553/edmunds-tesla-model-3-ev-of-year/|title=Edmunds Declares Tesla Model 3 Its Top-Rated Electric Car Of The Year|date=December 12, 2019|accessdate=December 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215065500/https://insideevs.com/news/387553/edmunds-tesla-model-3-ev-of-year/|archive-date=December 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>

In late 2019, the Model 3 was also named a Top Safety Pick+ by the [[Insurance Institute for Highway Safety|IIHS]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.caranddriver.com/news/a29117057/tesla-model-3-iihs-top-safety-pick-plus/|title=2019 Tesla Model 3 Named IIHS Top Safety Pick Plus|work=[[Car and Driver]]|last=Sky Brown|first=Laura|date=September 19, 2019|accessdate=September 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920123728/https://www.caranddriver.com/news/a29117057/tesla-model-3-iihs-top-safety-pick-plus/|archive-date=September 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The Model 3 also won Car of the Year in Denmark, Car of the Year 2020 in Norway, and Swiss Car of the Year 2020. <ref>{{cite web |title=Tesla model 3 Wiki - Tesla Model 3 Awards |url=https://www.teslamodel3wiki.com/tesla-model-3-awards/ |website=Tesla Model 3 Wiki |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>

The Model 3 was named as UK Car of the Year 2020 by a panel of 29 motoring journalists. The director of the awards stated that the car's "technology, performance and range" were converting opinions in favour of electric vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Hudson|first=Paul|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/cars/news/tesla-model-3-takes-uk-car-year-title/|title=Tesla Model 3 takes UK Car of the Year title|date=2020-02-28|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2020-02-28|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref>

